<statement>
<image width="33%"  pi:generated="problems/images/8d7b5bd582ddbeed8cc8954a29ffe3b4.png" /><p>
Suppose a = 2 and c = 9. Calculate:</p>
<p>
b = <fillin characters="20" /></p>
<p>
A = <fillin characters="20" /> degrees</p>
<p>
B = <fillin characters="20" /> degrees</p>
<p>
Round all answers to one decimal place. Give angles in <em>degrees</em>.
</p>
</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>8.8</li><li>12.8</li><li>77.2</li></ul></p><p>First calculate the length of the other leg.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{9}^{{2}}={2}^{{2}}+{b}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{81}={4}+{b}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{81}-{4}={b}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{77}={b}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle\sqrt{{{77}}}={b}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{8.7749643873921}\approx{b}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{8.8}\approx{b}</m>.</p>
<p>For angle A</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{\arcsin{{\left(\frac{{2}}{{9}}\right)}}}\approx{12.839588406891}\approx{12.8}</m></p>
<p>For angle B</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{\arccos{{\left(\frac{{2}}{{9}}\right)}}}\approx{77.160411593109}\approx{77.2}</m></p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

